articles.title: Background/Training
articles.description: I attended the University of Virginia for undergrad, where I was first exposed to R during an intro biostatistics course. After graduating with a bachelors in Human Biology, I joined the Peace Corps as a community health educator. Unfortunately, due to the pandemic, I was evacuated out of Ethiopia after 14 months. My Peace Corps experience sparked my interest in public health and led me to join JHSPH.

articles.title: Five Fun Facts About Me
articles.description:
-- I have a 1 year old Doberman! 

-- I’m from a small town in south Georgia but don’t have a Southern accent.

-- I can’t function without a steady stream of caffeine.

-- My favorite Ethiopian dish is kitfo. 

-- I just moved to Baltimore this summer and welcome any recommendations for restaurants, activities, etc.

articles.title: My Website
articles.contents:
About Me
My name is Mareike and I’m a MSPH student in the global disease epidemiology and control program. I’m completing certificates in Vaccine Science and Policy, Humanitarian Health, and Evaluation of International Health Programs.

articles.title: Cool Website
articles.description:
I received a GHEFP to work with CHAMPS Bangladesh at icddr,b. This team is part of a global surveillance network that works to generate and share cause of death data on child mortality. It’s really exciting and fascinating work, so check it out! 
https://champshealth.org/sites-bangladesh/
